-- WH Group updates Hong Kong IPO filing, trims sponsors to two
-- By Denny Thomas and Daniel Stanton
-- Thu Jul 10, 2014 12:52AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, July 10 (Reuters) - Chinese pork producer WH Group Ltd <0288.HK>, which earlier this year a pulled its up to $5.3 billion Hong Kong initial public offering, has updated its prospectus in a sign the company could relaunch the offer soon.

WH Group, whose products include Smithfield ham and Farmland bacon in the United States, has named BOC International and Morgan Stanley <MS.N> as the two IPO sponors, down from an initial list of seven.